            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`win_draw_end()` doesn't check if grid line exceeds `w_view_width`. Previously `grid_line_start()` used `w_grid.cols` to limit columns, but now `GridView` only stores the start of the viewport, not its size:\n```c\ntypedef struct {\n  ScreenGrid *target;\n  int row_offset;\n  int col_offset;\n} GridView;\n```\nand `grid_line_start()` instead uses the entire grid's width as `grid_line_maxcol`.\n\nSo to fix this, should `GridView` also store the viewport size, or should `win_draw_end()` pass `w_view_width` to `grid_line_start()`?",
